Excessive requirements for public procurement applications are excluded by law
The legislation may establish exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurements.
In the autumn session of the plenary meeting, the State Duma plans to consider in the second reading a bill establishing the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, which can only be participants of small and medium-sized enterprises.
The amendments are made by the government to the law "On purchases of goods, works, services of certain types of legal entities".
The draft law was developed in compliance with the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-sized Enterprises in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents, which the customers have the right to require in the context of the application from the participants of the procurement - small and medium-sized enterprises.
And also about the list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On purchases of goods, works, services by individual types of legal entities" is framed by the purchasing activities of individual types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, registration and composition of the application for participation in the purchase are established by the customers independently in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, the customers establish excessive requirements for the content, the submission of the application, the mandatory presence in its composition of certificates, certificates, excerpts, the period of receipt of which in the authorized authorities is the period of the acquisition of the goods and the parties will be compared with the period of the submission of applications, which leads to inconvenience.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents, which the customers have the right to demand as part of the application from the participants of the procurement, which are the subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises.
"Acceptance of the document will allow to exclude the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants, which are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises," - said in the explanatory note.
